  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nRunning `lighthouse --version` prints \"Lighthouse\" twice, which looks weird (see below). Similarly for `lighthouse -h`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ lighthouse -h\r\nLighthouse Lighthouse/v0.2.0/f26adc0a\r\nSigma Prime <contact@sigmaprime.io>\r\n...\r\n$ lighthouse --version\r\nLighthouse Lighthouse/v0.2.0/f26adc0a\r\nBLS Library: blst\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nSee above\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nLighthouse printed twice.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nLighthouse printed once.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nThe `--version` option would be easy to fix, just change the format string. The `--help` might required digging around in clap configuration.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, change the `VERSION` constant so that it's just the `v0.2.0/f26adc0a` part and add the Lighthouse prefix when constructing the default graffiti\r\n",
