    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "So our official version string is: `Lighthouse/v0.2.0/f26adc0a`, but `clap` decides to prefix it with the name of the `clap::App`, which gives us `Lighthouse Lighthouse/v0.2.0/f26adc0a`.\r\n\r\nWe want to avoid going into the `common/lighthouse_version` crate and just stripping the `Lighthouse` there, because then it will be missing for the API and P2P network. Ideally we can just tell `clap` not to prefix the version string.",
